<h1>SRIRAM IAS Admin Panel<br>Finance Operations Module — Detailed Flow Guide</h1>

<p class="meta"><strong>Document version:</strong> 1.0 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Date:</strong> May 26, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Scope:</strong> Frontend UI/UX flows (mock/demo data until APIs are connected)</p>

<div class="note">
<strong>Important:</strong> This guide describes the enhanced Finance Operations module built on top of the existing admin panel design. Navigation between finance sub-modules uses the <strong>left sidebar</strong> (Finance Operations submenu). The horizontal tab bar and demo banner were removed per UI preference.
</div>

<h2>1. Architecture Overview</h2>

<h3>1.1 Entry point</h3>
<ul>
<li>URL base: <strong>/finance</strong> redirects to <strong>/finance/dashboard</strong>.</li>
<li>Layout wrapper: <strong>FinanceLayout.jsx</strong> — wraps all finance routes and provides <strong>FinanceOperationsProvider</strong> for linked actions.</li>
<li>Authentication: User must be logged in (<strong>ProtectedRoute</strong>). Role-based access uses <strong>RoutePermissionGuard</strong> and <strong>financePermissions.js</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.2 Shared services (how modules stay linked)</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Component / File</th><th>Role in the flow</th></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceOperationsContext</td><td>Opens student finance profile drawer; navigates between finance routes (e.g. reports → verification).</td></tr>
<tr><td>financeRecordModel.js (enrichFinanceRecord)</td><td>Normalizes payment rows with center, batch, verification status, EMI status, GST, UTR, audit fields.</td></tr>
<tr><td>financeAPI.js</td><td>Single API layer; uses mock data when backend is offline (VITE_FINANCE_USE_MOCK / isFrontendOnly).</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceCenterFilterContext</td><td>Center scope from header/sidebar — dashboard and aggregates respect selected center(s).</td></tr>
<tr><td>financeExport.js</td><td>CSV, Excel, Print, PDF with standard ERP export columns on all major tables.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>1.3 User roles and permissions</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Role</th><th>Finance capabilities (summary)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Super Admin</td><td>Full access including GST settings.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Operation Admin</td><td>View, edit payments, approve, export, EMI, receipts — not GST edit.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Center Admin</td><td>View, approve, export, receipts; center locked to their center.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Counseling Admin</td><td>View, export, receipts — limited edit/approve.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>2. Module-by-Module Flows</h2>

<h3>2.1 Payment Dashboard (/finance/dashboard)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Executive overview of collections, pending amounts, EMI, offline approvals, and center performance.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>User opens sidebar → Finance Operations → Payment Dashboard.</li>
<li>Page loads via <strong>useFinanceDashboard</strong> → <strong>fetchPaymentDashboardByScope</strong> using center filter + course + month filters.</li>
<li>While loading: <strong>FinanceDashboardSkeleton</strong> displays.</li>
<li>User sees:
<ul>
<li>Center chips (All Centers + selected centers) synced with header center selector.</li>
<li>Filters: Course, Month, Batch.</li>
<li>KPI stat cards: Total revenue, Today's collections, Pending revenue, Total due, Overdue, Failed, EMI active, Offline approvals pending, Verification pending, Monthly collections, Success rate.</li>
<li>Charts: Monthly revenue, Payment status breakdown, Course-wise revenue.</li>
<li>Center ranking (overall view) → click opens <strong>CenterDrillDownModal</strong>.</li>
<li>Tables: Recent successful payments; Recent failed/pending.</li>
<li>Quick actions: Verify Payment, Receipts, Send Reminder, Reports, Export dashboard.</li>
<li>Recent finance activity feed.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Refresh: Banner refresh icon reloads data (auto-refresh every 60s in hook).</li>
<li>Export: Downloads CSV of recent payments using standard export columns.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Links to other modules:</strong> Quick actions route to Verification, Receipts, Communication, Reports. Center drill-down ties to center-wise reporting.</p>

<h3>2.2 Student Payment Reports (/finance/reports)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Master ledger of all student payments with advanced filtering and CRUD-style actions.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load all payment reports via <strong>fetchPaymentReports</strong> (enriched mock/API data).</li>
<li>User filters by: search, payment status, type, mode, course, branch, center, batch, state, date range, student ID, mobile.</li>
<li>Table shows columns: Student, Center, Course, Batch, Status, Verification, EMI, amounts, receipt, date, etc. (column visibility toggle).</li>
<li>Row actions:
<ul>
<li><strong>View</strong> → PaymentViewDrawer (read-only detail, receipt actions).</li>
<li><strong>Edit</strong> (if permitted) → PaymentEditModal → updatePaymentStatus → toast → reload.</li>
<li><strong>Receipt</strong> → generateReceipt.</li>
<li><strong>Reminder</strong> → sendPaymentReminder (queues communication log entry in mock).</li>
<li><strong>Profile</strong> / linked icons → StudentFinanceProfilePanel (tabbed drawer).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Export toolbar: CSV, Excel, Print, PDF for <strong>filtered</strong> rows only.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Business flow (intended when API live):</strong> Payment record created → appears in reports → verification if needed → receipt generated → communication sent.</p>

<h3>2.3 Payment Verification Center (/finance/verification)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Finance team reviews pending/partial payments before marking as paid.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Queue loaded via <strong>fetchVerificationQueue</strong> (built from payments with Pending/Partial status).</li>
<li>Filter by verification status and search (student, course, ID, UTR).</li>
<li>For each row user can:
<ul>
<li><strong>View proof</strong> → ProofViewerModal (screenshot/PDF placeholder, UTR, notes).</li>
<li><strong>Approve</strong> → updatePaymentStatus (Paid) → optional generateReceipt → reload queue.</li>
<li><strong>Reject</strong> → updatePaymentStatus (Rejected).</li>
<li><strong>Reupload</strong> → requestVerificationReupload (Escalated in mock).</li>
<li>Linked actions → profile, receipts, attempts, communication.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Export queue for audit.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Status flow:</strong> Pending Verification → Under Review → Approved / Rejected / Escalated (reupload).</p>

<h3>2.4 EMI Management (/finance/emi)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Manage installment plans per student/course.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load plans via <strong>fetchEmiPlans</strong>.</li>
<li>Summary cards: Active plans, Total pending, Due installments.</li>
<li>Search filters student/course/ID.</li>
<li>EMI plans table: progress bar, pending amount; pencil opens <strong>EmiEditModal</strong> (if canManageEmi).</li>
<li>In modal: edit installments (dates, amounts, status Due/Paid/Overdue), add/remove rows, save → <strong>updateEmiPlan</strong>.</li>
<li>Second table lists all installments across plans.</li>
<li>Export plans via toolbar.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Linked flow:</strong> When EMI installment paid (API): generate receipt → email/WhatsApp/SMS via communication module.</p>

<h3>2.5 Receipt Management (/finance/receipts)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Central receipt registry — generate, preview, resend.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load payments with amount or receipt number via <strong>fetchPaymentReports</strong> filtered.</li>
<li>Search by receipt #, student, payment ID.</li>
<li>Actions per row:
<ul>
<li><strong>Preview</strong> → ReceiptPreview modal.</li>
<li><strong>Generate</strong> (no receipt yet) → generateReceipt.</li>
<li><strong>Resend</strong> → resendReceipt (Email channel in UI).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Export receipt list.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Center-wise numbering:</strong> GST settings define per-center receipt/invoice prefixes used when API generates numbers.</p>

<h3>2.6 Student Finance Profiles (/finance/profiles)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> List view of students with finance summary; detailed view in drawer.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load profiles via <strong>fetchStudentFinanceProfiles</strong>.</li>
<li>Search by name, ID, mobile.</li>
<li>Profile table + flattened course history table.</li>
<li>Click pencil → FinanceSlideDrawer with note field (mock save).</li>
<li>From any finance page: <strong>StudentFinanceProfilePanel</strong> (global drawer) with tabs:
<ul>
<li>Overview — totals, EMI status, last payment.</li>
<li>Payment History — course-level payments.</li>
<li>EMI — link to EMI Management.</li>
<li>Receipts — receipt numbers.</li>
<li>Communication — log entries.</li>
<li>Verification — status per payment.</li>
<li>Failed Attempts — link to attempt logs.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>

<h3>2.7 Payment Attempt Logs (/finance/attempts)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Audit trail for gateway failures and retries.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load via <strong>fetchPaymentAttemptLogs</strong> (derived from payment attempt arrays in mock).</li>
<li>Filter: search, status (Success/Failed), mode (UPI/Card).</li>
<li>Columns: Student, Course, Attempt #, Txn ID, Gateway status/message, Amount, Date.</li>
<li>Export for analysis.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Future actions (UI-ready concept):</strong> Retry payment link, escalate, send payment link.</p>

<h3>2.8 Offline Payment Approval (/finance/offline-approval)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Students upload cash/UPI/bank proof; finance approves manually.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load <strong>fetchOfflineApprovals</strong>.</li>
<li>Stat cards: Pending, Total, Approved count.</li>
<li>Default filter: Pending Approval.</li>
<li>For pending rows (if canApprove):
<ul>
<li>Preview proof → ProofViewerModal.</li>
<li>Approve → approveOfflinePayment (Approved).</li>
<li>Reject → approveOfflinePayment (Rejected).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Linked profile/actions on row.</li>
<li>Export requests.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Status flow:</strong> Uploaded → Pending Approval → Approved / Rejected.</p>

<h3>2.9 Payment Communication Logs (/finance/communication)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Track and send payment-related messages.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Top form: Send reminder — mobile, email, channel (WhatsApp/Email/SMS) → <strong>sendPaymentReminder</strong> → new log entry in mock.</li>
<li>Table: Log ID, Type, Recipient, Channel, Status, Sent time.</li>
<li>Filter by channel and search.</li>
<li>Export logs.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Links:</strong> Receipt resend, EMI reminders, verification notifications all intended to appear here when API connected.</p>

<h3>2.10 GST &amp; Invoice Settings (/finance/gst-settings)</h3>
<p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Per-center tax and document configuration.</p>

<p><strong>User flow:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Load <strong>fetchGstSettings</strong>.</li>
<li>Global section: GST %, invoice prefix, receipt prefix, tax enabled toggle.</li>
<li>Per-center rows (branchGst from CENTER_SEED): GST number, state code, invoice/receipt prefix, finance manager, address, footer (logo/signature when API supports upload).</li>
<li>Save (Super Admin / canManageGst only) → <strong>updateGstSettings</strong>.</li>
<li>Other roles: fields read-only, save hidden.</li>
</ol>

<p><strong>Downstream effect:</strong> Receipt and invoice generation use these prefixes per center when live.</p>

<h2>3. End-to-End ERP Flow (All Modules Connected)</h2>

<ol>
<li><strong>Student enrolls</strong> → fee assigned (profiles / reports show total fees).</li>
<li><strong>Payment initiated</strong> (online) → attempt logs capture success/failure.</li>
<li><strong>Or offline proof uploaded</strong> → offline approval queue.</li>
<li><strong>Verification</strong> if status pending/partial → verification center.</li>
<li><strong>Approval</strong> → payment status Paid → receipt generated in receipt management.</li>
<li><strong>Communication</strong> → receipt/reminder sent → logged in communication.</li>
<li><strong>EMI path</strong> → partial payment → EMI plan → installments tracked in EMI management.</li>
<li><strong>Reporting</strong> → dashboard aggregates + student payment reports + exports.</li>
<li><strong>GST</strong> → center settings applied to invoice/receipt documents.</li>
</ol>

<h2>4. UI Components Reference</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Component</th><th>Used on</th></tr>
<tr><td>FinancePageShell</td><td>All pages — PageBanner + title + optional actions</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceExportToolbar</td><td>Dashboard, Reports, Verification, EMI, Receipts, Attempts, Offline, Communication</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceFilterPanel</td><td>Verification, Offline (search + status filters)</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceLinkedActions</td><td>Reports, Verification, Offline rows</td></tr>
<tr><td>FinanceStatusBadge</td><td>All tables — color-coded statuses</td></tr>
<tr><td>PaginatedFigmaTable</td><td>All list views — pagination, sticky header option</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>5. QA &amp; Testing Assets</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>docs/qa/finance-operations-test-cases.csv</strong> — original test cases (may need refresh).</li>
<li><strong>docs/qa/finance-operations-test-cases-v2.csv</strong> — updated cases for new features (linked drawer, export toolbar, proof viewer).</li>
<li><strong>docs/qa/frontend-test-cases.csv</strong> — full admin panel test suite.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. What Was Removed (UI)</h2>
<ul>
<li>FinanceDemoBanner (blue demo data alert) — removed from layout.</li>
<li>FinanceRouteTabs (horizontal button grid) — removed; use sidebar only.</li>
</ul>

<h2>7. Backend Integration Checklist (When APIs Go Live)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Point financeAPI.js to real endpoints; set VITE_FINANCE_USE_MOCK=false.</li>
<li>Enforce server-side RBAC matching financePermissions keys.</li>
<li>Wire file upload for offline/verification proofs to ProofViewerModal URLs.</li>
<li>Persist GST logo/signature per center.</li>
<li>Real-time updates for dashboard (optional WebSocket/polling).</li>
<li>Connect communication delivery status (opened, failed).</li>
</ol>

<p class="meta">End of document — SRIRAM IAS Admin Panel Finance Operations Flow Guide</p>

</body>
